
    length()
String tweet = "Liz Lemon, ninjas are kind of cool... I just dont know any personally. Get on that.";  

    // What's the character count?
System.out.println(tweet.length());
    
    
    concat()
String name = "Code";

name = name.concat("cademy");

System.out.println(name);


    equals()
String password = "correcthorsebatterystaple";
String realPassword = "Correcthorsebatterystaple";
   
System.out.println(password.equals(realPassword));//prints false
System.out.println(password.equalsIgnoreCase(realPassword));//prints true

Side note, thereâ€™s also a equalsIgnoreCase() method that compares two strings without considering upper/lower cases.


    indexOf()  FINDING INDEX
String letters = "ABCDEFGHIJKLMN";
System.out.println(letters.indexOf("C"));

String letters = "ABCDEFGHIJKLMN";
System.out.println(letters.indexOf("EFG"));

    charAt()   WITH INDEX FIND CHARACTORS
String firstName = "Mei";  
String lastName = "Wang";
    
// What are the initials?
System.out.println(firstName.charAt(0) );
    
    substring()
String line = "The Heav'ns and all the Constellations rung";     
  
System.out.println(line.indexOf("Constel"));//24
System.out.println(line.indexOf("rung"));//39
System.out.println(line.substring(24, 38));


toUpperCase() / toLowerCase()

String hashtag = "#100DaysOfCode";
    
System.out.println(hashtag.toLowerCase());//#100daysofcode

System.out.println(hashtag.toUpperCase());//#100DAYSOFCODE
    
